   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES795093184" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP STATICHTML" -->
   <p>I carefully ripped the message off the page and affixed it to the seat in front of me on the bus. I thought, let this be a reminder to anyone who reads it!</p>   <p>I took a photo of the note and posted it to my Instagram. Looking back at the image later that night, I realized who the message was really for. Myself.</p>   <p><em>Malaka Gharib is a writer and editor on NPR's science desk and the author of </em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Was-Their-American-Dream-Graphic/dp/0525575111/ref=tmm_pap_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=">I Was Their American Dream: A Graphic Memoir</a>.</p>
</div>
